                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I'm amazed at how many people I group with don't time their buffs (including pickup, guild and raid.)  Is it that difficult?  At 65, most of the buffs are group buffs anyway.  Don't they see them wearing off on themselves?
<br />

<br />
This is one of my pet peeves and if you group with me, in any situation, you RARELY have to ask me for a buff (unless I died or you died and the timers are off).  If you do have to ask me, you need only ask once and it's done a.s.a.p.  Same with my druid and cleric.
<br />

<br />
I buff pets without being asked, as soon as they are cast.  I give bards cha and I give liching necros gift.  I make sure humans/barbs can see in the dark too, etc.
<br />

<br />
I was on a raid Sun. playing my cleric.  The raid asked for haste no less than 5 times.  At the end of the raid, haste had not once been cast on anyone.  (I razzed my guild telling them they needed to deal with that once in a while to ensure they don't start taking me for granted.)
<br />

<br />
Last night, I played my druid on a raid because we needed healers.  Right before we started moving, the necro in my group says, "8 min. left on Replenishment".  LOL Yeah, so?  For some reason, this both tickled and irritated me and I've thought of it several times between then and now.
<br />

<br />
I think maybe the new buff timers are the debil. <img src="images/smiles/icon_wink.gif" alt="icon_wink.gif" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
I was just wondering how many of the rest of you are conscientious in keeping buffs up.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><span style="color: indigo"><span style="font-size: 18px; line-height: normal">Jianna</span></span>
<br />
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=143587" target="_blank" class="postlink">65 High Elf Coercer</a>
<br />
<a href="http://www.ancientones.org" target="_blank" class="postlink">Ancient Ones of Xegony</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
