                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Don't they see them wearing off on themselves? 
<br />
</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
In raids and to some extent groups, you are casting on other groups which refreshes ONLY your timer, so there is no way to keep track of everyone elses.  If a buff goes thery can send me a tell in raid or ask in grp, same as I do.  There is no problems with that.
<br />

<br />
In a group IF I notice vallons going, I refresh it, if not the tank will let me know very quickly.  Also on raids I often click off Vallons to free up buff slots so I have no clue when it is going to wear off.
<br />

<br />
On raids it's a good idea to buff by tells for those rezzed (if someone isn't asigned to that) and for those that arrive late.  
<br />

<br />
