                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I used to keep track of buff timers on everyone, back when I was raiding hate with 20 other people. Nowdays with 50+ person raids and 3 or 4 other encs buffing people it's silly to even consider. I buff people as soon as they send a tell and people appreciate the fast response. I use <a href="http://www.eqwatcher.com/" target="_blank" class="postlink">EQWatcher</a> to make a sound every time someone sends me a tell which is very helpful in not missing requests while I'm playing 3 characters.
<br />

<br />
That said, I never buff people that just ask in raid channel for buffs. Mostly that only comes from guests as we have trained all the guild members. The only buff people are allowed to ask for in channel is DI if their cleric doesn't have it up... <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">will just AE again and wipe c5 off them again, hi trash in Txevu</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
